Ubuntu Laravel + Blender Setup Guide

This guide is written for Ubuntu (Server or Desktop).  
It’s meant for Laravel-based projects like:

- BLOXCREATE / BLOXCITY  
- Laravel Roblox Clone  
- Vextoria  
- BrickPlanet  

Repositories you can use:

BLOXCREATE / BLOXCITY  
https://github.com/RobinShinny/BLOXCREATE-BLOXCITY  

Laravel Roblox Clone  
https://github.com/foxxosnoot/laravel-roblox-clone  

Vextoria  
https://github.com/closure-exlosure/Vextoria-Src  

BrickPlanet  
https://github.com/im-aeo/brickplanet  

Yes, this setup will also work for BrickPlanet.


--------------------------------------------------
1. Installing Blender (System Wide)
--------------------------------------------------

Blender should never be installed inside /var/www.  
It should be installed globally so Apache (www-data) can run it properly.

Run this:

cd ~
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y bzip2 wget

sudo apt remove -y blender
sudo rm -f /usr/bin/blender

wget https://download.blender.org/release/Blender2.79/blender-2.79b-linux-glibc219-x86_64.tar.bz2
tar -xjf blender-2.79b-linux-glibc219-x86_64.tar.bz2

sudo mv blender-2.79b-linux-glibc219-x86_64 /opt/blender279
sudo ln -sf /opt/blender279/blender /usr/bin/blender

Now test it:

blender --version
sudo -u www-data blender --version

If both work, you're good.

Blender should remain in:
 /opt/blender279


--------------------------------------------------
2. Cloning Your Laravel Project
--------------------------------------------------

Go into your web directory:

cd /var/www

Clone whichever project you want:

sudo git clone https://github.com/RobinShinny/BLOXCREATE-BLOXCITY bloxcreate
sudo git clone https://github.com/foxxosnoot/laravel-roblox-clone laravel-roblox-clone
sudo git clone https://github.com/closure-exlosure/Vextoria-Src vextoria
sudo git clone https://github.com/im-aeo/brickplanet brickplanet

Then go into the project:

cd /var/www/html
put it in here
(or whichever one you cloned)


--------------------------------------------------
3. Install Laravel Dependencies
--------------------------------------------------

Inside the project folder:

composer install
cp .env.example .env
php artisan key:generate

After that, open the .env file and set your database credentials correctly.


--------------------------------------------------
4. Fix Permissions (Important for Laravel)
--------------------------------------------------

Laravel only needs write access to:

- storage
- bootstrap/cache

Run this inside the project folder:

sudo chown -R www-data:www-data .
sudo chmod -R 775 storage
sudo chmod -R 775 bootstrap/cache

If your project uses uploads or thumbnails:

cd public
sudo mkdir -p uploads
sudo mkdir -p thumbnails

sudo chown -R www-data:www-data uploads
sudo chown -R www-data:www-data thumbnails
sudo chmod -R 775 uploads
sudo chmod -R 775 thumbnails

Then clear Laravel cache:

cd ..
php artisan config:clear
php artisan cache:clear
php artisan view:clear


--------------------------------------------------
5. Apache Configuration (Ubuntu)
--------------------------------------------------

On Ubuntu, Apache site configs are located at:

/etc/apache2/sites-available/

Most people edit:

/etc/apache2/sites-available/000-default.conf

Open it:

sudo nano /etc/apache2/sites-available/000-default.conf

You can use something like this if you understand what it does:

<VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerName localhost
    ServerAdmin webmaster@localhost
    DocumentRoot /var/www/html/public
    DirectoryIndex index.php

    <Directory /var/www/html/public>
        Options Indexes FollowSymLinks
        AllowOverride All
        Require all granted
    </Directory>

    ErrorLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/laravel_error.log
    CustomLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/laravel_access.log combined
</VirtualHost>

<VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerName servers.user-aim.xyz
    DocumentRoot /var/www/html/renderer

    <Directory /var/www/html/renderer>
        Options FollowSymLinks
        AllowOverride All
        Require all granted
    </Directory>

    ErrorLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/renderer_error.log
    CustomLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/renderer_access.log combined
</VirtualHost>

<VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerName cdn.user-aim.xyz
    DocumentRoot /var/www/storage

    <Directory /var/www/storage>
        Options -Indexes +FollowSymLinks
        AllowOverride None
        Require all granted
    </Directory>

    <FilesMatch "\.php$">
        Require all denied
    </FilesMatch>

    ErrorLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/cdn_error.log
    CustomLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/cdn_access.log combined
</VirtualHost>

After editing:

sudo a2enmod rewrite
sudo systemctl restart apache2

If something breaks, check:

sudo tail -50 /var/log/apache2/error.log


--------------------------------------------------
Important Things to Remember
--------------------------------------------------

- This is for Ubuntu.
- It works for BLOXCREATE, BLOXCITY, Vextoria, Laravel Roblox Clone, and BrickPlanet.
- Apache must point to the project’s /public folder.
- Only storage and bootstrap/cache need write permissions.
- Blender must stay in /opt.
- Keep each Laravel project in its own separate folder.
- Don’t chmod 777 everything.
- Don’t blindly copy Apache configs without understanding them.

If everything is set up correctly:
Laravel will run,
BrickPlanet will work,
the renderer will function,
CDN will serve safely,
